#Analysis using the source


encodeSource <- function(x) {
  if(grepl(">Twitter for iPhone</a>", x)){
    "iphone"
  }else if(grepl(">Twitter for iPad</a>", x)){
    "ipad"
  }else if(grepl(">Twitter for Android</a>", x)){
    "android"
  } else if(grepl(">Twitter Web Client</a>", x)){
    "Web"
  } else if(grepl(">Twitter for Windows Phone</a>", x)){
    "windows phone"
  }else if(grepl(">dlvr.it</a>", x)){
    "dlvr.it"
  }else if(grepl(">IFTTT</a>", x)){
    "ifttt"
  }else if(grepl(">Facebook</a>", x)){ 
    
    "facebook"
  }else {
    "others"
  }
}


chuchuDF$tweetSource = sapply(chuchuDF$statusSource, encodeSource)
## Error in lapply(X = X, FUN = FUN, ...): object 'chuchuDF' not found

#Create a wordcloud from the screenName

pal <- brewer.pal(8, "Dark2")
pal <- pal[-(1:4)]
set.seed(123)

par(mar = c(0,0,0,0), mfrow = c(1,1))

wordcloud(words = Corpname, scale=c(3,0.5),
          max.words=500,
          random.order=FALSE,
          rot.per=0.5,
          use.r.layout=TRUE,
          colors=pal)
